description: Tuktu Resources Ltd. engages in the exploration for and development of base and precious metals in Canada. The company explores for lead, zinc, silver, gold, copper, molybdenum, and tungsten properties. It holds interests in the Isintok property; Vowell Creek property that consists of 12,750.20 hectares located in south of Golden, British Columbia; and McFarlane property located in Kootenay Lake, British Colombia. The company was formerly known as Jasper Mining Corporation and changed its name to Tuktu Resources Ltd. in October 2022. Tuktu Resources Ltd. was incorporated in 1994 and is headquartered in Calgary, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Timothy A. de Freitas Ph.D.
